KLX Inc. Key Developments

KLX Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended April 30, 2017; Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Fiscal 2017
May 24 17
KLX Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended April 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company's revenues were $411.3 million compared with $352.8 million a year ago. The increase was driven by a 10.0% increase in revenues in the Aerospace Solutions Group segment and a 72.4% increase in revenues in the Energy Services Group segment. Operating earnings were $48.6 million compared with $23.2 million a year ago. Earnings before income taxes were $29.6 million compared with $4.3 million a year ago. Net earnings were $18.4 million or $0.36 per basic and diluted share compared with $2.5 million or $0.05 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash flows provided by operating activities was $20.0 million compared with $41.4 million a year ago. Capital expenditures were $14.5 million compared with $19.2 million a year ago. Adjusted earnings before tax expense was $40.3 million compared with $13.8 million a year ago. Adjusted net earnings were $34.8 million or $0.67 per diluted share compared with $13.8 million or $0.26 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $71.0 million compared with $44.6 million a year ago.

For fiscal 2017, the company's revenues are expected to increase approximately 17% to $1.75 billion, operating earnings are expected to increase approximately 72% to $222 million, adjusted net earnings are expected to increase approximately 68% to $157 million, adjusted net earnings per diluted share is expected to increase approximately 68% to $3.00 per diluted share.


